article.linkText: Heise scores 25, Northern Iowa defeats Prairie View A&M 74-55
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- — Nate Heise's 25 points helped Northern Iowa defeat Prairie View A&M 74-55 on Tuesday night. Heise added 10 rebounds for the Panthers (4-7). Tytan Anderson scored 17 points and added seven rebounds. Bowen Born shot 4 for 9, including 3 for 8 from beyond the arc to finish with 13 points. The Panthers (4-5) were led in scoring by Javontae Hopkins, who finished with 13 points and eight rebounds. Prairie View A&M also got 11 points and two steals from Kevin McGaskey. In addition, Chris Felix Jr. had 10 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
